news.title: U.S. housing market cooling as building permits tumble, starts fall
news.para: Homebuilding was already being constrained by soaring prices as well as shortages of materials. The housing market is the sector of the economy most sensitive to interest rates, with building permits a leading indicator for the sector.

news.title: Lucknow development body takes back 14 acre green belt from hotel
news.para: “On completion of the lease period and alleged violation of lease terms by the hotel management, LDA vice-chairman Akshay Tripathi cancelled the allotment of the land,” read the LDA statement.

news.title: China: New home prices fall in April for the first time since Dec as Covid bites
news.para: Average new-home prices in 70 major cities fell 0.2% on a month-on-month basis, compared with zero growth in March, according to Reuters calculations based on April data from the National Bureau of Statistics (NBS).

news.title: Encroachment upon railway land: Uttarakhand HC asks for property documents
news.para: ​After hearing the matter, the division bench of Justice Sarad Kumar Sharma and Justice RC Khulbe asked residents of the colony to present all their property documents within two weeks when the case will next be heard.

news.title: Indore: Building permission of 16 units in Pragati Green Colony revoked
news.para: According to IMC commissioner Pratibha Pal, the decision to revoke the building permission of 16 under-construction structures in Pragati Green Colony under ward 76 of zone 19 was taken for violating set approvals.

news.title: Ajmera Realty's profit at Rs 14 crore in Q4 FY22
news.para: Total income rose to Rs 183.62 crore in the fourth quarter of the last fiscal year from Rs 79.78 crore in the year-ago period, according to a regulatory filing.

news.title: Hundreds rendered homeless as BDA razes houses in Bareilly
news.para: ​​As per BDA officials, there are around 500 houses built on "4 hectare of illegally sold land" in Chandpur and Doharia villages on the outskirts of Bareilly, and all of them are under scanner now.

news.title: Nagpur: Over 22,000 more unauthorized plots crop up in two decades
news.para: As per the NIT data, the most number of applications (8,507) for regularization of 7,047 unauthorized plots came from east division followed by 6,959 for 5,507 from south division.

news.title: Maharashtra: 82 registration department officials under scanner
news.para: Data available with the registration department revealed that 47 of these officials were from Pune district, while the rest were from Thane and Aurangabad.

news.title: Credai meets Goa revenue minister, seeks ease of doing business
news.para: Credai Goa president Nilesh Salkar said the meeting was convened with the aim to “talk about the issues and concerns” that Goa’s builders have.

news.title: DDA issues notice to set up consortium for three sectors under land pooling
news.para: The DDA has also issued a public notice to all the land owners to register objections with reference to their list of pooled lands under the policy.

news.title: Mumbai: 1979 building shown as garden space in development plans, society pays heavily for BMC error
news.para: It was only around 2006-07 that the residents of Arun Cooperative Housing Society, most of them senior citizens, learnt of it when they wanted to go in for redevelopment.

news.title: Regulatory framework, robust returns set to prompt Indian REITs next growth phase
news.para: The country’s maiden REIT listed on bourses over three years ago on April 1, 2019 with Blackstone Group and Embassy Group taking their joint office assets platform Embassy Office Parks public.

news.title: DLF's sales bookings jumps over two-fold to Rs 7,273 crore during FY22
news.para: The company said this has been its strongest performance in the last 10 years. Its super luxury project 'The Camellias' continues to evince strong customer interest and delivered healthy sales bookings of Rs 2,550 crore during the last fiscal.

news.title: Preeti Chandra is flight risk, mastermind of conspiracy in passing info inside Tihar: ED to SC
news.para: Additional Solicitor General Madhavi Divan, appearing for ED, said that the application has been filed by Preeti at the time when the Supreme Court is on the cusp of going into summer vacation and she poses an enormous flight risk.
